     314           1 : GameBoyCore.prototype.OPCODE = [
     315           1 :   //NOP
     316           1 :   //#0x00:
     317          16 :   function (parentObj) {
     318          16 :     //Do Nothing...
     319          16 :   },
     320           1 :   //LD BC, nn
     321           1 :   //#0x01:
     322         528 :   function (parentObj) {
     323         528 :     parentObj.registerC = parentObj.memoryReader[parentObj.programCounter](parentObj, parentObj.programCounter);
     324         528 :     parentObj.registerB = parentObj.memoryRead((parentObj.programCounter + 1) & 0xFFFF);
     325         528 :     parentObj.programCounter = (parentObj.programCounter + 2) & 0xFFFF;
     326         528 :   },
     327           1 :   //LD (BC), A
     328           1 :   //#0x02:
     329           1 :   function (parentObj) {

    5693         226 : GameBoyCore.prototype.run = function () {
    5694         226 :   //The preprocessing before the actual iteration loop:
    5695         226 :   if ((this.stopEmulator & 2) == 0) {
    5696         226 :     if ((this.stopEmulator & 1) == 1) {
    5697         226 :       if (!this.CPUStopped) {
    5698         226 :         this.stopEmulator = 0;
    5699         226 :         this.drewFrame = false;
    5700         226 :         this.audioUnderrunAdjustment();
    5701         226 :         this.clockUpdate();      //RTC clocking.
    5702         226 :         if (!this.halt) {
    5703         226 :           this.executeIteration();
    5704         226 :         }
    5705         226 :         else {            //Finish the HALT rundown execution.
    5706         226 :           this.CPUTicks = 0;
    5707         226 :           this.calculateHALTPeriod();
    5708         226 :           if (this.halt) {
    5709         226 :             this.updateCoreFull();
    5710         226 :           }
    5711         226 :           else {
    5712         226 :             this.executeIteration();
    5713         226 :           }
    5714         226 :         }
    5715         226 :         //Request the graphics target to be updated:
    5716         226 :         this.requestDraw();
    5717         226 :       }
    5718         226 :       else {
    5719         226 :         this.audioUnderrunAdjustment();
    5720         226 :         this.audioTicks += this.CPUCyclesTotal;
    5721         226 :         this.audioJIT();
    5722         226 :         this.stopEmulator |= 1;      //End current loop.
    5723         226 :       }
    5724         226 :     }
    5725         226 :     else {    //We can only get here if there was an internal error, but the loop was restarted.
    5726         226 :       cout("Iterator restarted a faulted core.", 2);
    5727         226 :       pause();
    5728         226 :     }
    5729         226 :   }
    5730         226 : }

    5732         213 : GameBoyCore.prototype.executeIteration = function () {
    5733         213 :   //Iterate the interpreter loop:
    5734         213 :   var opcodeToExecute = 0;
    5735         213 :   var timedTicks = 0;
    5736         213 :   while (this.stopEmulator == 0) {
    5737         213 :     //Interrupt Arming:
    5738         213 :     switch (this.IRQEnableDelay) {
    5739         213 :       case 1:
    5740         213 :         this.IME = true;
    5741         213 :         this.checkIRQMatching();
    5742         213 :       case 2:
    5743         213 :         --this.IRQEnableDelay;
    5744         213 :     }
    5745         213 :     //Is an IRQ set to fire?:
    5746         213 :     if (this.IRQLineMatched > 0) {
    5747         213 :       //IME is true and and interrupt was matched:
    5748         213 :       this.launchIRQ();
    5749         213 :     }
    5750         213 :     //Fetch the current opcode:
    5751         213 :     opcodeToExecute = this.memoryReader[this.programCounter](this, this.programCounter);
    5752         213 :     //Increment the program counter to the next instruction:
    5753         213 :     this.programCounter = (this.programCounter + 1) & 0xFFFF;
    5754         213 :     //Check for the program counter quirk:
    5755         213 :     if (this.skipPCIncrement) {
    5756         213 :       this.programCounter = (this.programCounter - 1) & 0xFFFF;
    5757         213 :       this.skipPCIncrement = false;
    5758         213 :     }
    5759         213 :     //Get how many CPU cycles the current instruction counts for:
    5760         213 :     this.CPUTicks = this.TICKTable[opcodeToExecute];
    5761         213 :     //Execute the current instruction:
    5762         213 :     this.OPCODE[opcodeToExecute](this);
    5763         213 :     //Update the state (Inlined updateCoreFull manually here):
    5764         213 :     //Update the clocking for the LCD emulation:
    5765         213 :     this.LCDTicks += this.CPUTicks >> this.doubleSpeedShifter;  //LCD Timing
    5766         213 :     this.LCDCONTROL[this.actualScanLine](this);          //Scan Line and STAT Mode Control
    5767         213 :     //Single-speed relative timing for A/V emulation:
    5768         213 :     timedTicks = this.CPUTicks >> this.doubleSpeedShifter;    //CPU clocking can be updated from the LCD handling.
    5769         213 :     this.audioTicks += timedTicks;                //Audio Timing
    5770         213 :     this.emulatorTicks += timedTicks;              //Emulator Timing
    5771         213 :     //CPU Timers:
    5772         213 :     this.DIVTicks += this.CPUTicks;                //DIV Timing
    5773         213 :     if (this.TIMAEnabled) {                    //TIMA Timing
    5774         213 :       this.timerTicks += this.CPUTicks;
    5775         213 :       while (this.timerTicks >= this.TACClocker) {
    5776         213 :         this.timerTicks -= this.TACClocker;
    5777         213 :         if (++this.memory[0xFF05] == 0x100) {
    5778         213 :           this.memory[0xFF05] = this.memory[0xFF06];
    5779         213 :           this.interruptsRequested |= 0x4;
    5780         213 :           this.checkIRQMatching();
    5781         213 :         }
    5782         213 :       }
    5783         213 :     }
    5784         213 :     if (this.serialTimer > 0) {                    //Serial Timing
    5785         213 :       //IRQ Counter:
    5786         213 :       this.serialTimer -= this.CPUTicks;
    5787         213 :       if (this.serialTimer <= 0) {
    5788         213 :         this.interruptsRequested |= 0x8;
    5789         213 :         this.checkIRQMatching();
    5790         213 :       }
    5791         213 :       //Bit Shit Counter:
    5792         213 :       this.serialShiftTimer -= this.CPUTicks;
    5793         213 :       if (this.serialShiftTimer <= 0) {
    5794         213 :         this.serialShiftTimer = this.serialShiftTimerAllocated;
    5795         213 :         this.memory[0xFF01] = ((this.memory[0xFF01] << 1) & 0xFE) | 0x01;  //We could shift in actual link data here if we were to implement such!!!
    5796         213 :       }
    5797         213 :     }
    5798         213 :     //End of iteration routine:
    5799         213 :     if (this.emulatorTicks >= this.CPUCyclesTotal) {
    5800         213 :       this.iterationEndRoutine();
    5801         213 :     }

    7341           1 : //Check for the highest priority IRQ to fire:
    7342          88 : GameBoyCore.prototype.launchIRQ = function () {
    7343          88 :   var bitShift = 0;

    7345          88 :   do {
    7346          88 :     //Check to see if an interrupt is enabled AND requested.
    7347          88 :     if ((testbit & this.IRQLineMatched) == testbit) {
    7348          88 :       this.IME = false;            //Reset the interrupt enabling.
    7349          88 :       this.interruptsRequested -= testbit;  //Reset the interrupt request.
    7350          88 :       this.IRQLineMatched = 0;        //Reset the IRQ assertion.

    7352          88 :       this.CPUTicks = 20;

    7354          88 :       this.stackPointer = (this.stackPointer - 1) & 0xFFFF;

    7356          88 :       this.stackPointer = (this.stackPointer - 1) & 0xFFFF;
    7357          88 :       this.memoryWriter[this.stackPointer](this, this.stackPointer, this.programCounter & 0xFF);

    7361          88 :       this.updateCore();

    7363          88 :     }
    7364          88 :     testbit = 1 << ++bitShift;

    7370        6816 : GameBoyCore.prototype.checkIRQMatching = function () {

    7375           1 : /*
    7376           1 :   Handle the HALT opcode by predicting all IRQ cases correctly,
    7377           1 :   then selecting the next closest IRQ firing from the prediction to
    7378           1 :   clock up to. This prevents hacky looping that doesn't predict, but
    7379           1 :   instead just clocks through the core update procedure by one which
    7380           1 :   is very slow. Not many emulators do this because they have to cover
    7381           1 :   all the IRQ prediction cases and they usually get them wrong.
    7382           1 : */
    7383          17 : GameBoyCore.prototype.calculateHALTPeriod = function () {
    7384          17 :   //Initialize our variables and start our prediction:
    7385          17 :   if (!this.halt) {
    7386          17 :     this.halt = true;
    7387          17 :     var currentClocks = -1;
    7388          17 :     var temp_var = 0;
    7389          17 :     if (this.LCDisOn) {
    7390          17 :       //If the LCD is enabled, then predict the LCD IRQs enabled:
    7391          17 :       if ((this.interruptsEnabled & 0x1) == 0x1) {
    7392          17 :         currentClocks = ((456 * (((this.modeSTAT == 1) ? 298 : 144) - this.actualScanLine)) - this.LCDTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7393          17 :       }
    7394          17 :       if ((this.interruptsEnabled & 0x2) == 0x2) {
    7395          17 :         if (this.mode0TriggerSTAT) {
    7396          17 :           temp_var = (this.clocksUntilMode0() - this.LCDTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7397          17 :           if (temp_var <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7398          17 :             currentClocks = temp_var;
    7399          17 :           }
    7400          17 :         }
    7401          17 :         if (this.mode1TriggerSTAT && (this.interruptsEnabled & 0x1) == 0) {
    7402          17 :           temp_var = ((456 * (((this.modeSTAT == 1) ? 298 : 144) - this.actualScanLine)) - this.LCDTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7403          17 :           if (temp_var <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7404          17 :             currentClocks = temp_var;
    7405          17 :           }
    7406          17 :         }
    7407          17 :         if (this.mode2TriggerSTAT) {
    7408          17 :           temp_var = (((this.actualScanLine >= 143) ? (456 * (154 - this.actualScanLine)) : 456) - this.LCDTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7409          17 :           if (temp_var <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7410          17 :             currentClocks = temp_var;
    7411          17 :           }
    7412          17 :         }
    7413          17 :         if (this.LYCMatchTriggerSTAT && this.memory[0xFF45] <= 153) {
    7414          17 :           temp_var = (this.clocksUntilLYCMatch() - this.LCDTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7415          17 :           if (temp_var <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7416          17 :             currentClocks = temp_var;
    7417          17 :           }
    7418          17 :         }
    7419          17 :       }
    7420          17 :     }
    7421          17 :     if (this.TIMAEnabled && (this.interruptsEnabled & 0x4) == 0x4) {
    7422          17 :       //CPU timer IRQ prediction:
    7423          17 :       temp_var = ((0x100 - this.memory[0xFF05]) * this.TACClocker) - this.timerTicks;
    7424          17 :       if (temp_var <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7425          17 :         currentClocks = temp_var;
    7426          17 :       }
    7427          17 :     }
    7428          17 :     if (this.serialTimer > 0 && (this.interruptsEnabled & 0x8) == 0x8) {
    7429          17 :       //Serial IRQ prediction:
    7430          17 :       if (this.serialTimer <= currentClocks || currentClocks == -1) {
    7431          17 :         currentClocks = this.serialTimer;
    7432          17 :       }
    7433          17 :     }
    7434          17 :   }
    7435          17 :   else {
    7436          17 :     var currentClocks = this.remainingClocks;
    7437          17 :   }
    7438          17 :   var maxClocks = (this.CPUCyclesTotal - this.emulatorTicks) << this.doubleSpeedShifter;
    7439          17 :   if (currentClocks >= 0) {
    7440          17 :     if (currentClocks <= maxClocks) {
    7441          17 :       //Exit out of HALT normally:
    7442          17 :       this.CPUTicks = Math.max(currentClocks, this.CPUTicks);
    7443          17 :       this.updateCoreFull();
    7444          17 :       this.halt = false;
    7445          17 :       this.CPUTicks = 0;
    7446          17 :     }
    7447          17 :     else {
    7448          17 :       //Still in HALT, clock only up to the clocks specified per iteration:
    7449          17 :       this.CPUTicks = Math.max(maxClocks, this.CPUTicks);
    7450          17 :       this.remainingClocks = currentClocks - this.CPUTicks;
    7451          17 :     }
    7452          17 :   }
    7453          17 :   else {
    7454          17 :     //Still in HALT, clock only up to the clocks specified per iteration:
    7455          17 :     //Will stay in HALT forever (Stuck in HALT forever), but the APU and LCD are still clocked, so don't pause:
    7456          17 :     this.CPUTicks += maxClocks;
    7457          17 :   }
    7458          17 : }

    9591           1 : function generateBlob(keyName, encodedData) {
    9592           0 :   //Append the file format prefix:
    9593           0 :   var saveString = "EMULATOR_DATA";
    9594           0 :   var consoleID = "GameBoy";
    9595           0 :   //Figure out the length:
    9596           0 :   var totalLength = (saveString.length + 4 + (1 + consoleID.length)) + ((1 + keyName.length) + (4 + encodedData.length));
    9597           0 :   //Append the total length in bytes:
    9598           0 :   saveString += to_little_endian_dword(totalLength);
    9599           0 :   //Append the console ID text's length:
    9600           0 :   saveString += to_byte(consoleID.length);
    9601           0 :   //Append the console ID text:
    9602           0 :   saveString += consoleID;
    9603           0 :   //Append the blob ID:
    9604           0 :   saveString += to_byte(keyName.length);
    9605           0 :   saveString += keyName;
    9606           0 :   //Now append the save data:
    9607           0 :   saveString += to_little_endian_dword(encodedData.length);
    9608           0 :   saveString += encodedData;
    9609           0 :   return saveString;
    9610           1 : }
    9611           1 : function generateMultiBlob(blobPairs) {
    9612           0 :   var consoleID = "GameBoy";
    9613           0 :   //Figure out the initial length:
    9614           0 :   var totalLength = 13 + 4 + 1 + consoleID.length;
    9615           0 :   //Append the console ID text's length:
    9616           0 :   var saveString = to_byte(consoleID.length);
    9617           0 :   //Append the console ID text:
    9618           0 :   saveString += consoleID;
    9619           0 :   var keyName = "";
    9620           0 :   var encodedData = "";
    9621           0 :   //Now append all the blobs:
    9622           0 :   for (var index = 0; index < blobPairs.length; ++index) {
    9623           0 :     keyName = blobPairs[index][0];
    9624           0 :     encodedData = blobPairs[index][1];
    9625           0 :     //Append the blob ID:
    9626           0 :     saveString += to_byte(keyName.length);
    9627           0 :     saveString += keyName;
    9628           0 :     //Now append the save data:
    9629           0 :     saveString += to_little_endian_dword(encodedData.length);
    9630           0 :     saveString += encodedData;
    9631           0 :     //Update the total length:
    9632           0 :     totalLength += 1 + keyName.length + 4 + encodedData.length;
    9633           0 :   }
    9634           0 :   //Now add the prefix:
    9635           0 :   saveString = "EMULATOR_DATA" + to_little_endian_dword(totalLength) + saveString;
    9636           0 :   return saveString;
    9637           1 : }
    9638           1 : function decodeBlob(blobData) {
    9639           0 :   /*Format is as follows:
    9640           0 :     - 13 byte string "EMULATOR_DATA"
    9641           0 :     - 4 byte total size (including these 4 bytes).
    9642           0 :     - 1 byte Console type ID length
    9643           0 :     - Console type ID text of 8 bit size
    9644           0 :     blobs {
    9645           0 :       - 1 byte blob ID length
    9646           0 :       - blob ID text (Used to say what the data is (SRAM/freeze state/etc...))
    9647           0 :       - 4 byte blob length
    9648           0 :       - blob length of 32 bit size
    9649           0 :     }
    9650           0 :   */
    9651           0 :   var length = blobData.length;
    9652           0 :   var blobProperties = {};
    9653           0 :   blobProperties.consoleID = null;
    9654           0 :   var blobsCount = -1;
    9655           0 :   blobProperties.blobs = [];
    9656           0 :   if (length > 17) {
    9657           0 :     if (blobData.substring(0, 13) == "EMULATOR_DATA") {
    9658           0 :       var length = Math.min(((blobData.charCodeAt(16) & 0xFF) << 24) | ((blobData.charCodeAt(15) & 0xFF) << 16) | ((blobData.charCodeAt(14) & 0xFF) << 8) | (blobData.charCodeAt(13) & 0xFF), length);
    9659           0 :       var consoleIDLength = blobData.charCodeAt(17) & 0xFF;
    9660           0 :       if (length > 17 + consoleIDLength) {
    9661           0 :         blobProperties.consoleID = blobData.substring(18, 18 + consoleIDLength);
    9662           0 :         var blobIDLength = 0;
    9663           0 :         var blobLength = 0;
    9664           0 :         for (var index = 18 + consoleIDLength; index < length;) {
    9665           0 :           blobIDLength = blobData.charCodeAt(index++) & 0xFF;
    9666           0 :           if (index + blobIDLength < length) {
    9667           0 :             blobProperties.blobs[++blobsCount] = {};
    9668           0 :             blobProperties.blobs[blobsCount].blobID = blobData.substring(index, index + blobIDLength);
    9669           0 :             index += blobIDLength;
    9670           0 :             if (index + 4 < length) {
    9671           0 :               blobLength = ((blobData.charCodeAt(index + 3) & 0xFF) << 24) | ((blobData.charCodeAt(index + 2) & 0xFF) << 16) | ((blobData.charCodeAt(index + 1) & 0xFF) << 8) | (blobData.charCodeAt(index) & 0xFF);
    9672           0 :               index += 4;
    9673           0 :               if (index + blobLength <= length) {
    9674           0 :                 blobProperties.blobs[blobsCount].blobContent =  blobData.substring(index, index + blobLength);
    9675           0 :                 index += blobLength;
    9676           0 :               }
    9677           0 :               else {
    9678           0 :                 cout("Blob length check failed, blob determined to be incomplete.", 2);
    9679           0 :                 break;
    9680           0 :               }
    9681           0 :             }
    9682           0 :             else {
    9683           0 :               cout("Blob was incomplete, bailing out.", 2);
    9684           0 :               break;
    9685           0 :             }
    9686           0 :           }
    9687           0 :           else {
    9688           0 :             cout("Blob was incomplete, bailing out.", 2);
    9689           0 :             break;
    9690           0 :           }
    9691           0 :         }
    9692           0 :       }
    9693           0 :     }
    9694           0 :   }
    9695           0 :   return blobProperties;
    9696           1 : }
